cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.GR, cs.RO 

This paper deals with point cloud analysis, which is a fundamental task in 3D computer vision. The paper proposes a method that combines global and local representations to address the issue of rotation invariance in point cloud classification. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a two-branch network for feature extraction, which involves machine learning techniques. Hence, it is also likely to belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper deals with 3D data, which involves geometric transformations, making it relevant to cs.GR (Graphics) and cs.RO (Robotics).
